abstract: Taliban fighters attacked Afghan government forces overnight, and militant commanders said on Monday insurgency operations would go-ahead until they receive fresh instructions based on a deal with the United States to reduce violence in the country.

lead_paragraph: KABUL — Taliban fighters attacked Afghan government forces overnight, and militant commanders said on Monday insurgency operations would go-ahead until they receive fresh instructions based on a deal with the United States to reduce violence in the country.
headline_main: No Let Up in Taliban Attacks, Fresh Orders Awaited Over Deal With U.S.
headline_print_headline: No Let Up in Taliban Attacks, Fresh Orders Awaited Over Deal With U.S.

abstract: For two months, Michael Bloomberg’s campaign has been preparing for a moment it knew would come: when decades of impolitic and insensitive remarks would face renewed scrutiny.
snippet: For two months, Michael Bloomberg’s campaign has been preparing for a moment it knew would come: when decades of impolitic and insensitive remarks would face renewed scrutiny.
lead_paragraph: HOUSTON — It hadn’t even been a full day since a 12-year-old video surfaced of Michael R. Bloomberg showing him linking the 2008 financial crisis to the end of redlining, a practice that allowed banks to declare low-income, mostly minority neighborhoods off-limits for loans.

headline_print_headline: Rivals Take Aim at Bloomberg, Armed With His Past Remarks

abstract: We seem to know less than we did at the beginning of the primary.
snippet: We seem to know less than we did at the beginning of the primary.
lead_paragraph: The Democratic presidential primary is starting to feel less like a political contest and more like an existential experiment. In the era of big data and after a year of micro-analyzing every little twist and turn, we seem to know less than we did at the beginning. In an era when we’re supposed to know everything, we somehow seem to know nothing.

abstract: What is the ultimate goal of Vladimir Putin’s announced plans to shake up the organization of Russia’s governance? Here’s one theory.
snippet: What is the ultimate goal of Vladimir Putin’s announced plans to shake up the organization of Russia’s governance? Here’s one theory.
lead_paragraph: In Russia, informal hierarchies tend to prevail over formal rules and procedures, or so we have long thought. Long-established democracies are different: They have traditions and regulations in place that set clear limits on nepotism and clan-based politics.

headline_main: Drop the Corruption, Keep the Authoritarianism

abstract: Scientists have dismissed suggestions that the Chinese government was behind the outbreak, but it’s the kind of tale that gains traction among those who see China as a threat.
snippet: Scientists have dismissed suggestions that the Chinese government was behind the outbreak, but it’s the kind of tale that gains traction among those who see China as a threat.
lead_paragraph: The rumor appeared shortly after the new coronavirus struck China and spread almost as quickly: that the outbreak now afflicting people around the world had been manufactured by the Chinese government.

abstract: President Donald Trump took a loop around the Daytona 500 racetrack on Sunday in his presidential limousine, drawing cheers from fans at NASCAR's most prestigious race not long after completing a dramatic flyby on Air Force One.
snippet: President Donald Trump took a loop around the Daytona 500 racetrack on Sunday in his presidential limousine, drawing cheers from fans at NASCAR's most prestigious race not long after completing a dramatic flyby on Air Force One.
lead_paragraph: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. — President Donald Trump took a loop around the Daytona 500 racetrack on Sunday in his presidential limousine, drawing cheers from fans at NASCAR's most prestigious race not long after completing a dramatic flyby on Air Force One.
headline_main: Trump Kicks Off Daytona 500 Race With Limo Loop, Air Force One Flyby
headline_print_headline: Trump Kicks Off Daytona 500 Race With Limo Loop, Air Force One Flyby

abstract: A growing number of Democratic lawmakers, union officials, state leaders and party strategists agree that Bernie Sanders is a risky nominee to put up against President Donald Trump. There's less agreement about whether — and how — to stop him.
snippet: A growing number of Democratic lawmakers, union officials, state leaders and party strategists agree that Bernie Sanders is a risky nominee to put up against President Donald Trump. There's less agreement about whether — and how — to stop him.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — A growing number of Democratic lawmakers, union officials, state leaders and party strategists agree that Bernie Sanders is a risky nominee to put up against President Donald Trump. There's less agreement about whether — and how — to stop him.
headline_main: One Thing Unites Establishment Democrats: Fear of Sanders
headline_print_headline: One Thing Unites Establishment Democrats: Fear of Sanders
